10. Dominica is a hub for indigenous communities and new spiritual beliefs

Earlier, the island of Dominica was home to the Romantic Abò indigenous tribe where BBC documented their lives by creating a tower oain modern society located right at the base of the Trafalgar Falls. However, these groups can sometimes still be found in isolated pockets on the islands performing some forms of a recast of this ancient way of life.

Although the country is a Roman Catholic country, embracing the new spiritual beliefs seen in only a few Caribbean islands such as America, England, and the Netherlands and working its way to become a place where the occults is brought to life! This makes Dominica a destination you can see and experience the juxtaposition of cultures.
